<p>Our PathPlanner paths worked around 40% of the time during our competition. While we were tethered it worked most of the time, but sometimes the beginning path which drives a small distance forward will turn to the left instead of going straight from the beginning. We’ve tried a handful of things such as recalibrating our navX with the buttons on the board. Our navX goes through calibration already every time the robot is started through code, we also make sure to reset the encoders/navX on the first trajectory which is recommended in the PathPlanner docs. I haven’t been able to replicate the bug where it turns to the left, it seems to just be random. Sometimes when we put it on the field it followed the path, other times it did the turn.</p>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2023-03-31T00:32:13.692Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":238,"reads":242,"readers_count":241,"score":1238.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":432471,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-sometimes-veers-off-path-from-the-beginning","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":57912,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-sometimes-veers-off-path-from-the-beginning/432471/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3177615,"name":"Gavin Matthews","username":"bovlb","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/bovlb/{size}/167232_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-31T00:38:40.562Z","cooked":"<p>It would help to have a link to your code, a video of the robot going wrong, and a screenshot showing what the odometry thinks is happening (e.g. <code>Field2d</code>).</p>
<p>Without those, it’s hard for us to help you, but some possible causes include motor inversion (say after brownout) and CANcoders with improperly glued magnets.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2023-03-31T00:38:40.562Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":235,"readers_count":234,"score":52.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":432471,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-sometimes-veers-off-path-from-the-beginning","display_username":"Gavin Matthews","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38743,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)"},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-sometimes-veers-off-path-from-the-beginning/432471/2","custom_user_title":"Programming mentor, Team 2102, RI, CSA (he/him)","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3177766,"name":"","username":"raspb3rry314","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/838e76/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-31T06:35:34.088Z","cooked":"<p>Sadly, I no longer have access to the robot as we already have shipped it. We were using fully charged batteries for every test and I did not see any brownouts. We use the NEO motor’s built-in encoders. We’ve tried the REV through-bore encoders but could not get the FRC system identification to work with them. I did check the logs after each of our matches and did notice that sometimes when the autonomous didn’t follow the path, during the autonomous period we would draw a lot more current compared to when it worked on the practice field. However, when we noticed that we re-used the same battery that the path worked at the practice field for our match and the robot didn’t follow the path.</p>
<p>Here is our drive code:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">package frc.robot.subsystems;

import com.kauailabs.navx.frc.AHRS;
import com.pathplanner.lib.PathPlannerTrajectory;
import com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PPRamseteCommand;
import com.revrobotics.CANSparkMax;
import com.revrobotics.CANSparkMax.IdleMode;
import com.revrobotics.CANSparkMaxLowLevel.MotorType;
import com.revrobotics.RelativeEncoder;
import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.PIDController;
import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.RamseteController;
import edu.wpi.first.math.controller.SimpleMotorFeedforward;
import edu.wpi.first.math.filter.LinearFilter;
import edu.wpi.first.math.geometry.Pose2d;
import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.DifferentialDriveKinematics;
import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.DifferentialDriveOdometry;
import edu.wpi.first.math.kinematics.DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.drive.DifferentialDrive;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.Command;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.InstantCommand;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SequentialCommandGroup;
import edu.wpi.first.wpilibj2.command.SubsystemBase;
import frc.robot.Constants;

public class Drive extends SubsystemBase {

  private CANSparkMax leftFrontCanSparkMax, leftRearCanSparkMax, rightFrontCanSparkMax, rightRearCanSparkMax;
  private RelativeEncoder leftEncoder, rightEncoder;
  private DifferentialDrive differentialDrive;
  private PIDController pidPitchController, pidDriveController;
  private AHRS navX;
  private LinearFilter speedLinearFilter, rotationLinearFilter;
  private DifferentialDriveKinematics driveKinematics;
  private DifferentialDriveOdometry driveOdometry;

  public Drive() {
    this.navX = new AHRS();

    this.leftFrontCanSparkMax = new CANSparkMax(Constants.LEFT_FRONT_SPARKMAX_PORT, MotorType.kBrushless);
    this.leftRearCanSparkMax = new CANSparkMax(Constants.LEFT_REAR_SPARKMAX_PORT, MotorType.kBrushless);
    this.rightFrontCanSparkMax = new CANSparkMax(Constants.RIGHT_FRONT_SPARKMAX_PORT, MotorType.kBrushless);
    this.rightRearCanSparkMax = new CANSparkMax(Constants.RIGHT_REAR_SPARKMAX_PORT, MotorType.kBrushless);
    this.leftFrontCanSparkMax.restoreFactoryDefaults();
    this.leftRearCanSparkMax.restoreFactoryDefaults();
    this.rightFrontCanSparkMax.restoreFactoryDefaults();
    this.rightRearCanSparkMax.restoreFactoryDefaults();

    this.leftFrontCanSparkMax.setIdleMode(IdleMode.kBrake);
    this.leftFrontCanSparkMax.setInverted(false);
    this.leftRearCanSparkMax.follow(this.leftFrontCanSparkMax);

    this.rightFrontCanSparkMax.setIdleMode(IdleMode.kBrake);
    this.rightFrontCanSparkMax.setInverted(true);
    this.rightRearCanSparkMax.follow(this.rightFrontCanSparkMax);

    this.leftEncoder = this.leftFrontCanSparkMax.getEncoder();
    this.leftEncoder.setPositionConversionFactor(Constants.POSITION_CONVERSION_FACTOR);
    this.leftEncoder.setVelocityConversionFactor(Constants.VELOCITY_CONVERSION_FACTOR);

    this.rightEncoder = this.rightFrontCanSparkMax.getEncoder();
    this.rightEncoder.setPositionConversionFactor(Constants.POSITION_CONVERSION_FACTOR);
    this.rightEncoder.setVelocityConversionFactor(Constants.VELOCITY_CONVERSION_FACTOR);

    this.rightRearCanSparkMax.burnFlash();
    this.rightFrontCanSparkMax.burnFlash();
    this.leftRearCanSparkMax.burnFlash();
    this.leftFrontCanSparkMax.burnFlash();

    this.differentialDrive = new DifferentialDrive(this.leftFrontCanSparkMax, this.rightFrontCanSparkMax);
    this.speedLinearFilter = LinearFilter.movingAverage(11);
    this.rotationLinearFilter = LinearFilter.movingAverage(5);

    this.driveKinematics = new DifferentialDriveKinematics(Constants.TRACK_WIDTH);
    this.driveOdometry = new DifferentialDriveOdometry(this.navX.getRotation2d(), this.leftEncoder.getPosition(), this.rightEncoder.getPosition());

    this.pidPitchController = new PIDController(Constants.PITCH_PID_P, 0, 0);
    this.pidDriveController = new PIDController(Constants.DRIVE_P, 0, 0);
  }

  @Override
  public void periodic() {
    this.driveOdometry.update(this.navX.getRotation2d(), this.getLeftEncoderPosition(), this.getRightEncoderPosition());
  }

  public void tankDrive(double leftInput, double rightInput) {
    this.differentialDrive.tankDrive(leftInput, rightInput);
  }

  public void tankDriveVoltage(double leftVoltage, double rightVoltage) {
    this.leftFrontCanSparkMax.setVoltage(leftVoltage);
    this.rightFrontCanSparkMax.setVoltage(rightVoltage);
    this.differentialDrive.feed();
  }

  public void arcadeDrive(double speed, double rotation) {
    this.differentialDrive.arcadeDrive(speedLinearFilter.calculate(speed), rotationLinearFilter.calculate(rotation));
  }

  public PIDController getPIDPitchController() {
    return this.pidPitchController;
  }

  public PIDController getPIDTurnController() {
    return this.pidTurnController;
  }

  public void calibrate() {
    this.navX.calibrate();
  }

  public double getAngle() {
    return this.navX.getRotation2d().getDegrees();
  }

  public float getPitch() {
    return this.navX.getPitch();
  }

  public double getLeftEncoderPosition() {
    return this.getLeftEncoder().getPosition();
  }

  public double getRightEncoderPosition() {
    return this.getRightEncoder().getPosition();
  }

  public double getLeftEncoderVelocity() {
    return this.getLeftEncoder().getVelocity();
  }

  public double getRightEncoderVelocity() {
    return this.getRightEncoder().getVelocity();
  }

  public RelativeEncoder getLeftEncoder() {
    return this.leftEncoder;
  }

  public RelativeEncoder getRightEncoder() {
    return this.rightEncoder;
  }

  public void reset() {
    this.navX.reset();
    this.leftEncoder.setPosition(0.0);
    this.rightEncoder.setPosition(0.0);
  }

  public DifferentialDriveKinematics getDriveKinematics() {
    return this.driveKinematics;
  }

  public void resetOdometry(Pose2d pose2d) {
    this.reset();
    this.driveOdometry.resetPosition(
        this.navX.getRotation2d(),
        this.getLeftEncoderPosition(),
        this.getRightEncoderPosition(),
        pose2d);
  }

  public DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds getWheelSpeeds() {
    return new DifferentialDriveWheelSpeeds(
        this.getLeftEncoderVelocity(), this.getRightEncoderVelocity());
  }

  public Pose2d getPose() {
    return this.driveOdometry.getPoseMeters();
  }

  public Command followTrajectoryCommand(PathPlannerTrajectory traj, boolean isFirstPath) {
    return new SequentialCommandGroup(
        new InstantCommand(
            () -&gt; {
              if (isFirstPath) {
                this.resetOdometry(traj.getInitialPose());
              }
            }),
        new PPRamseteCommand(
            traj,
            this::getPose,
            new RamseteController(2, 0.7),
            new SimpleMotorFeedforward(Constants.DRIVE_S, Constants.DRIVE_V, Constants.DRIVE_A),
            this.driveKinematics,
            this::getWheelSpeeds,
            this.pidDriveController,
            this.pidDriveController,
            this::tankDriveVoltage,
            true,
            this
        )
    );
  }
}
