<p>Are you saying that the path was followed in practice but then in competition, immediately after that practice session and without recharging the battery, the robot didn’t follow the practice?</p>
<p>That’s a depleted battery. And setting a voltage compensation level for any autonomous functions even with a fully charged battery can improve the reproducibility of the autonomous.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2023-03-31T11:41:21.487Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":173,"readers_count":172,"score":59.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":432471,"topic_slug":"pathplanner-sometimes-veers-off-path-from-the-beginning","display_username":"SLAB-Mr.Thomas","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":24594,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/pathplanner-sometimes-veers-off-path-from-the-beginning/432471/4","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3177822,"name":"Basel Alghanem","username":"Basel_A","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/basel_a/{size}/65204_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-31T12:31:33.159Z","cooked":"<p>Is it just a brief veer and then it follows the path properly? If yes, it could be that when you start the path, your wheels are initially aligned sideways instead of forwards. You can make sure your wheels are forward before starting the path.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2023-03-31T12:32: